    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p><strong>No</strong>, <a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/xmlschema-1/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">XML Schema (XSD)</a> is for validating <a href=\"https://www.w3.org/TR/REC-xml/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><em><strong>XML</strong></em></a>; to validate <a href=\"http://www.json.org/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><em><strong>JSON</strong></em></a>, see <a href=\"http://json-schema.org/\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">JSON Schema</a>.</p>\n<p>I recommend generating schemas by hand for full understanding and full control over the constraints.  However, here are some automated tools that can jumpstart the process:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>To convert from JSON Schema to XSD, see <a href=\"https://github.com/ethlo/jsons2xsd\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">jsons2xsd</a>.</li>\n<li>To convert from XSD to JSON Schema, see <a href=\"https://github.com/highsource/jsonix-schema-compiler/wiki\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Jsonix Schema Compiler</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Related and also very useful:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>To parse from XML to JSON (unmarshal) or serialize JSON to XML\n(marshal), see <a href=\"https://github.com/highsource/jsonix\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">JSONIX</a>.</li>\n<li>For a list of implementations, including validators in various languages, see <a href=\"http://json-schema.org/tools.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">JSON Schema Tooling</a>.</li>\n</ul>\n"
  }, {
